{
  "texts": [
    "On GLUE, we use the train set for fine-tuning and the dev set for accuracy evaluation.",
    "For santacoder, we evaluate performance using HumanEval [7] and report pass@1 scores.",
    "All experiments were conducted using PyTorch on a single Nvidia A100 (40GB) GPU.In MLFS, the Low rank matrices are added on the QKV vectors and the intermediate size of feedforward network (FFN) layers.",
    "We set β l = 0.1 ∀l in feature distillation loss and choose distillation factor α = 0.9.",
    "For training, we use a maximum sequence length of 128; effective batch size of 128 for QQP, MNLI, QNLI, and 64 for the other data sets."
  ]
}